FOWLER RIDGE IV WIND FARM LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Fowler Ridge Wind Farm LLC ("Fowler Ridge IV") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Fowler Ridge IV generating facility ("Fowler Ridge IV Facility").
The Fowler Ridge IV Facility is a wind generating facility located in Benton County, Indiana. The Fowler Ridge IV Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Indiana Michigan Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Fowler Ridge IV's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Fowler Ridge IV Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Fowler Ridge IV's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Fowler Ridge IV shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $574,999.20. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $47,916.60.
